# Formatting

## format

> `format(formatters)`

Apply Python format strings to column values. Use standard Python format mini-language.

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `formatters` | dict[str, str] | — | Mapping of column name → format string |

Common format strings:

| Format string | Example input | Example output |
|---------------|---------------|----------------|
| `"{:.2f}"` | `3.14159` | `3.14` |
| `"{:,.0f}"` | `1234567` | `1,234,567` |
| `"{:.1f}B"` | `250.3` | `250.3B` |
| `"{:+.1f}%"` | `12.5` | `+12.5%` |
| `"{:06.2f}"` | `3.1` | `003.10` |

**Example:**

```python
df.style().format({
    "Revenue": "{:.1f}B",
    "Growth": "{:+.1f}%"
}).show()
```

